posts.body: I'm sorry to inform you that the spectrogram you posted is of a 44.1kHz upconvert. The mirror images in the high frequency range are a giveaway.

Multi quality is bad for a p2p network. When you have multiple different copies of the same video floating around, it results in swarm fragmentation and poor performance/availibility. Just man up and get fast internet.

posts.subject: Do posts on 08chan ever expire?
posts.body: If they don't, 08chan will eventually become too big for most users.

>>2c73e615-9c13-4af6-b55c-007cbf9d0616
The files are only downloaded when you open the board. Never open the board = never download the files.

posts.subject: Production Music
posts.body:
ITT we post our favorite production music. 

> What is production music
Production music (also known as stock music or library music) is the name given to recorded music that can be licensed to customers for use in film, television, radio and other media.

> Where can I find production music
Old production music on CD and vinyl can be bought on ebay.
https://www.universalproductionmusic.com/ has 100k+ tracks (they claim) all available for free preview. The preview quality is 112k mp3 but their API also returns links to 192k AAC copies of the music. With a bit of scripting, you can scrape tons of reasonably good quality music from there.

I'll start with some more well known ones.

Interlude: used 80's tv show The Joy of Painting. 
Deadlines: BIG BILL HELL'S CARS!
Chardonnay: Sampled in vaporwave track  Nouveau Life™ ‎- New World™ - 01 - Start Life

>>91c2e469-db23-40cb-b0ba-94a2388959f5
Why would anyone host a free speech forum on a Chinese service?
When the government starts legislating social rules, you know society is falling apart.

The West gave China access to our markets hoping that prosperity will lead to political liberalization. That didn't work at all, and we should stop doing it. We need to deal with China the way we dealt with the Soviets while we still have the technological lead. If China catches up and achieves technological independence, we won't have the leverage anymore and we will be screwed.

Even if they're really just banning accounts they lose money on, I think it's a good thing in the end because google has been pricing their video service below cost and it's anti-competitive. When they finally start charging an honest price, alternative video hosting platforms, some of which may be p2p, will be developed to replace google.

I don't know why the ZN peer count fluctuates so wildly. On some days, I only see a couple hundred nodes on ZeroTalk and less than 200 peers on 08chan. Today, I see 4000+ peers on ZeroTalk and over 1000 peers on 08chan.

No doubt there are ideologues on all sides. The internet echo chambers are partly to blame.

The like/dislike ratings that are so common on today's social sites need to be removed. Not all opinions are equally valid or logical. The voting features allow the ideologues to express their opinions without revealing the gaps in their thinking. If you have an opinion, say it like a man. Don't hide behind an anonymous vote count.
